thanks! that looks good. but i'm kinda worried about how it handles other stuff. like, what if the names are all caps or have weird spacing, or if the prices aren't formatted perfectly?

just to be safe, i'm gonna run it through a few more variations to see if it breaks. if it doesn't handle these, i'll need you to fix the logic.

run this:
test_data_2 = [
    {"id": "201", "prod_name": "  DARK BLUE WIDGET  ", "price_usd": "30.00", "in_stock": "yes"},
    {"id": "202", "prod_name": "small nail", "price_usd": "0.50", "in_stock": "no"}
]

expected_2 = [
    {"id": 201, "name": "Dark Blue Widget", "price": 30.0, "available": True},
    {"id": 202, "name": "Small Nail", "price": 0.5, "available": False}
]

can you make sure your function handles this too?
assert clean_metadata(test_data_2) == expected_2

